LuaScript:
sand_GUID = "22d13a"
golf_ball_master_GUID = "779a0f"

--Each zone covers all or a portion of a hole_pars
--They are used to determine which hole the players ball is currently at for automatic stroke calculations
hole_number_zones = {
    ["59ec01"] = 1,
    ["b57941"] = 2,
    ["bba0d8"] = 3, ["5a3a14"] = 3,
    ["c90f60"] = 4,
    ["2b6956"] = 5,
    ["de1f38"] = 6,
    ["6ac3da"] = 7, ["d235b2"] = 7,
    ["3bfeea"] = 8, ["8deca9"] = 8,
    ["721964"] = 9, ["8c5b9f"] = 9,
    ["e9cd9b"] = 10, ["e91d10"] = 10, ["34b3bf"] = 10,
    ["bce6cd"] = 11, ["cd3450"] = 11, ["407dd4"] = 11, ["cf5e12"] = 11,
    ["1a74c9"] = 12, ["2f45cf"] = 12,
    ["f4ea31"] = 13,
    ["c7a69e"] = 14,
    ["72543c"] = 15,
    ["7c568d"] = 16,
    ["2efdca"] = 17,
    ["fbdacf"] = 18,
}

skee_ball_zones = {
    ["933a28"] = -3,
    ["9c4aa8"] = -3,
    ["07f38c"] = -2,
    ["a4cbec"] = -1,
    ["6e287b"] = 0,
    ["f9f5d0"] = 1,
    ["de2485"] = 2,
    ["96c3c4"] = 3,
}

guids_to_freeze = {
    "8e9d89", "22d13a", "9a127a", "779a0f"
}

--The pars for each hole that are to be used to populate the score card and score bar
hole_pars = {
    1, 2, 2, 2, 2, 1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 2, 1, 2, 4, 2, 4, 4, "X"
}

--This is a special mechanism for hole 9 that has 3 seperate holes to drop into 3 possible areas
--This links the zones with the drop positions when needed
hole_drop_zones = {
    guid = { "19caf4", "2f85b8", "56ff3c" },
    output_position = { vector(3.00, 4.60, 46.25), vector(-1.00, 4.60, 46.25), vector(-5.00, 4.60, 46.25) }
}

score_card_visible = {}

messages = {
    welcome = "\nWelcome to [19a36b][b]Tabletop Mini Golf 2[/b][-]!\n[i]For help type -mghelp in the log or chat window.\nConfigure custom keyboard commands under Options -> Game Keys[/i]",
    help = "[19a36b][b]Tabletop Minigolf 2 Help[/b][-]\n[b][i][How to Play][/i][/b]\n1. Grab a ball from one of the baskets.\n2. Place the ball at the start of the first hole.\n3. Use the flick tool to hit the ball towards the hole.\n4. Continue playing the holes until you finish.\n5. The player with the lowest score wins!\n\n[b][i][Controls][/i][/b]\nThis mod uses a new feature - Game Keys - found in the top bar under Options -> Game Keys to use certain features. You can customise these controls to best suit you.\n"
}

score_card_height = 191
score_card_middle_height = 129
score_card_player_height = 38

function onLoad(save_state)
    local data = JSON.decode(save_state)

    if data ~= nil and data.player_data ~= nil then
        player_data = data.player_data
        updateAllScoreBars()
        updateFullScoreCard()
    else
        initPlayerData()
    end

    Physics.setGravity(vector(0, -60, 0))
    initScoreCard()
    initGameObjects()

    addHotkey("Show Score Card", showScoreCardPressed)
    addHotkey("Add stroke", addStrokePressed)
    addHotkey("Remove stroke", removeStrokePressed)
    addHotkey("Reset Game (Host Only)", resetGame)

    displayWelcomeMessageToAll()

    freezeObjects()
end

function onSave()
    local data = {
        ["player_data"] = player_data
    }

    return JSON.encode(data)
end

function initPlayerData()
    local colors = Player.getAvailableColors()
    player_data = {}
    for color_index = 1, #colors do
        local color = colors[color_index]
        player_data[color] = {
            ["current_hole"] = 0,
            ["hole_score"] = {},
            ["total_score"] = 0
        }
        score_card_visible[color] = false
    end
end

function initScoreCard()
    initScoreCardPar()
    local colors = Player.getAvailableColors()
    local seated_colors = getSeatedPlayers()

    for i = 1, #colors do
        removePlayerScoreCard(colors[i])
    end

    Wait.frames(function()
        for i = 1, #seated_colors do
            addPlayerScoreCard(seated_colors[i])
        end
    end, 1)
end

function freezeObjects()
    for i = 1, #guids_to_freeze do
        local object = getObjectFromGUID(guids_to_freeze[i])
        object.interactable = false
    end
end

function onPlayerChangeColor(player_color)
    if player_color == "Grey" then
        local seated = getSeatedPlayers()
        local colors = Player.getAvailableColors()
        for i = 1, #colors do
            if seated[colors[i]] == nil and self.UI.getAttribute("ScoreCard_" .. colors[i], "active") == "true" then
                removePlayerScoreCard(colors[i])
            end
        end
    else
        addPlayerScoreCard(player_color)
    end
end

function initScoreCardPar()
    local total_par = 0
    for i = 1, 17 do
        self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCardPar_" .. i, "text", hole_pars[i])
        total_par = total_par + hole_pars[i]
    end
    self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCardPar_18", "text", "X")
    self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCardParTotal", "text", total_par)
end

function onObjectEnterScriptingZone(zone, enter_object)
    if isGolfBall(enter_object) then
        ballEnterScriptingZone(zone, enter_object)
    end
end

function onObjectSpawn(object)
    if isGolfBall(object) then
        initGolfBall(object)
    end
end

function onObjectPickUp(player_color,  picked_up_object)
    if isGolfBall(picked_up_object) then
        setGolfBallOwner(picked_up_object, player_color)
    end
end

function onObjectLeaveContainer(container, leave_object)
    if leave_object.getGMNotes() == "Golf Ball" then
        Wait.frames(|| golfBallLeaveContainer(leave_object), 2)
    end
end

function golfBallLeaveContainer(ball)
    ball.setLuaScript(golf_ball_master.getLuaScript())
    Wait.frames(|| setGolfBallOwner(ball, ball.held_by_color), 2)
end

function setGolfBallOwner(ball, color)
    ball.setVar("owner_color", color)
end

function ballEnterScriptingZone(zone, enter_object)
    if hole_number_zones[zone.getGUID()] ~= nil then
        local hole_number = hole_number_zones[zone.getGUID()]
        local color = enter_object.getVar("owner_color")

        if color == nil then
            return false
        end

        if color ~= nil then
            setCurrentHole(color, hole_number)
            updateScoreBar(color)
        end
    elseif skee_ball_zones[zone.getGUID()] ~= nil then
        local color = enter_object.getVar("owner_color")
        skeeBallScore(color, skee_ball_zones[zone.getGUID()])
        enter_object.destruct()
    else
        ballEnterDropZone(zone, enter_object)
    end
end

function onPlayerConnect(player)
    displayWelcomeMessage()
end

function displayWelcomeMessage()
    printToColor(messages.welcome, player.color)
end

function displayWelcomeMessageToAll()
    printToAll(messages.welcome)
end

function onChat(message, player)
    if message == "-mghelp" then
        printToColor(messages.help, player.color, Table)
    end
end

function skeeBallScore(color, value)
    modifyStroke(color, value)
    local total = player_data[color].total_score
    printToAll(Player[color].steam_name .. " as " .. color .. " scored " .. value .. " on hole 18 and finished with a final score of " .. total .. "!")
end

function ballEnterDropZone(zone, enter_object)
    for i = 1, 3 do
        if hole_drop_zones.guid[i] == zone.getGUID() then
            Wait.time(function()
                enter_object.setPosition(hole_drop_zones.output_position[i])
                enter_object.setVelocity(vector(0, 0, -3 + math.random(2)))
            end, 1)
        end
    end
end

function showScoreCardPressed(color)
    score_card_visible[color] = not score_card_visible[color]
    updateScoreCardVisibility()
end

function scoreShowClicked(player)
    score_card_visible[player.color] = not score_card_visible[player.color]
    updateScoreCardVisibility()
end

function addStrokePressed(color)
    modifyStroke(color, 1)
end

function removeStrokePressed(color)
    modifyStroke(color, -1)
end

function resetGame(color)
    if Player[color].host then
        initPlayerData()
        initScoreCard()
        updateAllScoreBars()
        updateFullScoreCard()
        broadcastToAll("Resetting game.", { 0.9, 0.1, 0.1})
    end
end

function updateFullScoreCard()
    local colors = Player.getAvailableColors()
    for i = 1, #colors do
        local color = colors[i]
        for i = 1, 18 do
            self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCardStrokes_" .. i .. "_" .. color, "text", player_data[color].hole_score[i] or "")
        end
        self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCardTotal_" .. color, "text", player_data[color].total_score or "")
        self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCardName_" .. color, "text", Player[color].steam_name or "")
    end
end

function updateScoreCardVisibility()
    local visibility_string = getScoreCardVisibilityString()
    self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCard", "visibility", visibility_string)
end

function getScoreCardVisibilityString()
    local colors = Player.getAvailableColors()
    local visibility_string = ""
    for i = 1, #colors do
        if score_card_visible[colors[i]] then
            visibility_string = visibility_string .. colors[i] .. "|"
        end
    end

    local len = string.len(visibility_string)

    if len > 0 then
        visibility_string = string.sub(visibility_string, 0, len - 1)
    else
        visibility_string = " "
    end

    return visibility_string
end

function initGameObjects()
    sand = getObjectFromGUID(sand_GUID)
    golf_ball_master = getObjectFromGUID(golf_ball_master_GUID)
end

function isGolfBall(object)
    return object.getGMNotes() == "Golf Ball"
end

function initGolfBall(ball_object)
    Wait.frames(||ball_object.registerCollisions(), 2)
end

function ballFlicked(args)
    local color = args.color
    local current_hole = player_data[color].current_hole
    if current_hole ~= 18 then
        modifyStroke(color, 1)
    end
end

function scoreBarPlusClicked(args)
    local color = args.color
    modifyStroke(color, 1)
end

function scoreBarPlusClicked(player, mouse_button)
    if mouse_button == "-1" then
        scoreBarClicked(player.color, 1)
    end
end

function scoreBarMinusClicked(player, mouse_button)
    if mouse_button == "-1" then
        scoreBarClicked(player.color, -1)
    end
end

function scoreBarClicked(color, value)
    local current_hole = getCurrentHole(color)

    if current_hole ~= nil and current_hole > 0 and current_hole ~= 18 then
        modifyStroke(color, value)
    end
end

function addPlayerScoreCard(color)
    local active = self.UI.getAttribute("ScoreCard_" .. color, "active")
    if active == "false" then
        modifyPlayerScoreCard(color, true)
    end
end

function removePlayerScoreCard(color)
    local active = self.UI.getAttribute("ScoreCard_" .. color, "active")
    if active == "true" then
        modifyPlayerScoreCard(color, false)
    end
end

function modifyPlayerScoreCard(color, active)
    local seated = getSeatedPlayers()
    local gap_size = score_card_player_height * #seated
    local score_card_modified = tostring(score_card_height + gap_size)
    local score_card_middle_modified = tostring(score_card_middle_height + gap_size)

    self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCard_" .. color, "active", tostring(active))
    self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCardName_" .. color, "text", Player[color].steam_name)
    self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCard", "height", score_card_modified)
    self.UI.setAttribute("ScoreCardMiddleFill", "height", score_card_middle_modified)

end

function modifyStroke(color, value)
    local data = player_data[color]
    if data.current_hole == 18 then
        if data.hole_score[data.current_hole] ~= nil then
            data.total_score = data.total_score - data.hole_score[data.current_hole]
        end
        data.hole_score[data.current_hole] = value
        data.total_score = data.total_score + value
        updateScoreBar(color)
        updateScoreCard(color, data.current_hole, data.hole_score[data.current_hole], data.total_score)
    elseif data.current_hole > 0 then
        if data.hole_score[data.current_hole] == nil then
            data.hole_score[data.current_hole] = 1
            data.total_score = data.total_score + 1
        elseif data.hole_score[data.current_hole] + value < 0 then
            data.hole_score[data.current_hole] = 0
        else
            data.hole_score[data.current_hole] = data.hole_score[data.current_hole] + value
            data.total_score = data.total_score + value
        end
        updateScoreBar(color)
        updateScoreCard(color, data.current_hole, data.hole_score[data.current_hole], data.total_score)
    end
end

function updateAllScoreBars()
    local colors = Player.getAvailableColors()
    local color = nil

    for color_index = 1, #colors do
        color = colors[color_index]
        if color ~= "Black" and Player[color].seated then
            updateScoreBar(color)
        end
    end
end

function updateScoreCard(color, hole, value, total_score)
    local id = "ScoreCardStrokes_" .. hole .. "_" .. color
    local id2 = "ScoreCardTotal_" .. color
    self.UI.setAttribute(id, "text", value)
    self.UI.setAttribute(id2, "text", total_score)
end

function updateScoreBar(color)
    local id = nil
    local current_hole = getCurrentHole(color)

    if current_hole == nil or current_hole == 0 then
        id = color .. "_ScoreBarHoleValue"
        self.UI.setAttribute(id, "text", "")
        id = color .. "_ScoreBarParValue"
        self.UI.setAttribute(id, "text", "")
        id = color .. "_ScoreBarStrokesValue"
        self.UI.setAttribute(id, "text", "")
        return false
    end

    local hole_score = getHoleScore(color, current_hole)

    local par = getHolePar(current_hole)

    id = color .. "_ScoreBarHoleValue"
    self.UI.setAttribute(id, "text", current_hole)
    id = color .. "_ScoreBarParValue"
    self.UI.setAttribute(id, "text", par)
    id = color .. "_ScoreBarStrokesValue"
    self.UI.setAttribute(id, "text", hole_score)
end

function getCurrentHole(color)
    return player_data[color].current_hole
end

function setCurrentHole(color, value)
    player_data[color].current_hole = value
end

function getHoleScore(color, hole)
    return player_data[color].hole_score[hole] or 0
end

function setHoleScore(color, hole, value)
    player_data[color].hole_score[hole] = value
    updateScoreCard(color, hole, value)
end

function getHolePar(hole)
    return hole_pars[hole]
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Assetbundle
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
--Golf Ball
owner_color = nil
detect_timer = nil
default_drag = 0.35
default_angular_drag = 0.7
sand_drag = 10
sand_angular_drag = 10

function onLoad(save_state)
    local data = JSON.decode(save_state)
    if save_state ~= "" then
        owner_color = data.owner_color
    end
    startDetectTimer()
end

function onSave()
    local data = {
        ["owner_color"] = owner_color
    }

    return JSON.encode(data)
end

function onFlick(color)
    Global.call("ballFlicked", {color = color})
    startDetectTimer()
end

function onDrop()
    startDetectTimer()
end

function startDetectTimer()
    detect_timer = Wait.time(interactWithTerrain, 0.1, 0)
end

function interactWithTerrain()
    if self.resting then
        inSand(false)
        return false
    end

    local hit = castDown()
    inSand(isHitSandy(hit))

    Wait.time(interactWithTerrain, 0.1, 0)
end

function isHitSandy(hit)
    local sand = Global.getVar("sand")
    return isObjectInHit(hit, sand)
end

function isObjectInHit(hit, object_to_find)
    for i = 1, #hit do
        if hit[i].hit_object == object_to_find then
            return true
        end
    end

    return false
end

function castDown()
    return Physics.cast({
        origin     = self.getPosition(),
        direction    = vector(0, -1, 0),
        type         = 1,
        max_distance = 1.3
    })
end

function inSand(in_sand)
    if in_sand then
        self.drag = sand_drag
        self.angular_drag = sand_angular_drag
    else
        self.drag = default_drag
        self.angular_drag = default_angular_drag
    end
end
